Package: TaxaMatch
Title: Store and Standardize Biological Match Data
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: person("Kevin", "Lafferty", , "klafferty@usgs.gov", role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: Stores and standardizes raw match data produced by external tools that
    compare biological observations (eDNA sequences, images, acoustic recordings) against
    reference databases. Outputs a canonical match object (one row per sample x reference
    match, with standard column names) for input to TaxaLikely. Match data sources include
    DNA barcode programs (e.g. MiFish), image classifiers, and acoustic recognizers.
    Score-to-likelihood conversion and reference quality assessment live in TaxaLikely.
    Part of the TaxaID ecosystem.
